The book "OS/2 2.11  Unleashed" states that the Media Vision Proaudio 16 
or the newer Proaudio Studio 16 work the best under OS/2. They further 
state that these two cards are the ONLY ones that support sharing between 
applications under OS/2. I personally have the Studio 16 at it does as 
the book  says under OS/2 Warp.  
Media Vision recently emerged from under Chapter 11 Banckruptcy and are 
back in the sound card business. The PS16 or Studio 16 are no longer 
being MFG; however, I still see many ads for them in computer magazines. 
They are still available in the distribution channels.

PA 16's go for $69-89 US and the Studio 16's go for $120-130 US.

