 I haven't found any problems with my SB16asp with Waveblaster daughterboard.
Amazing! The one thing that has been ok. They have a mixer just for OS/2 and
they are the basis for compatibility for everything else. The SB16asp have a
better signal to noise ratio than the AWE32 but the AWE has chorus and reverb 
and you can make your own samples (they have 512KB compressed on the board and
SB16 has 4 meg. uncompress) if ;you are going to use your own Reverb etc. I 
recommend the 16ASP.

